Compactification 

We have found potentially long-lived orbits for probe antibranes
moving in the field of  source branes, provided  and
so they move in 3 transverse dimensions. For 10 dimensions
overall, this is what singles out D6-branes for special attention.
For later applications to brane-world cosmology we will be
interested in branes whose world-volume is 4 dimensional, and so
we pause here to consider how this may be achieved from the above
solutions by compactification.

Toroidal Reduction 

Our goal in this section is to dimensionally reduce the action,
eq. eq:EFbulkaction , from  to  dimensions. The
point is to present a consistent lower-dimensional truncation of
this action, in the sense that any solution of the
lower-dimensional equations of motion are also solutions of the
equations of the full system, eq. eq:EFbulkaction ,
following the construction of ref. .

